ActAppropriation Act No. 1, 2011-12
PrecisAppointment of YVES BRODEUR as Ambassador and Permanent Representative of Canada to the North Atlantic Council (NATO), in Brussels; GORDON CAMPBELL as High Commissioner for Canada to the United Kingdom of Great Britain and Northern Ireland; SANJEEV CHOWDHURY as Consul General of Canada in Rio de Janeiro, Federative Republic of Brazil; GLENN DAVIDSON as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of Canada to the Islamic Republic of Afghanistan; DAVID DEVINE as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of Canada to the Republic of Suriname, with residence in Georgetown; ELISSA GOLBERG as Ambassador and Permanent Representative of Canada to the Office of the United Nations and to the United Nations Conference on Disarmament, in Geneva; BENOÎT-PIERRE LARAMÉE as High Commissioner for Canada to the Republic of Cameroon; GARY LUTON as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of Canada to the State of Qatar; GUILLERMO RISHCHYNSKI as Ambassador and Permanent Representative of Canada to the United Nations, in New York; IVAN ROBERTS as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of Canada to Burkina Faso; MARIO-STE-MARIE as Consul General of Canada in Sydney, Commonwealth of Australia; and ROMAN WASCHUK as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of Canada to the Republic of Serbia, with concurrent accreditation to the Republic of Montenegro and to the Republic of Macedonia.
